│ prematurely, causing the assertion to fail. The power-of-2 condition should │
│ be evaluated first, as it's independent of element type validity.\n\n4.     │
│ **Proposed Edit Point(s)**: Reorder checks in `hasFullVectorsOrPowerOf2` to │
│ test `has_single_bit(Sz)` before the `isValidElementType` check. This       │
│ ensures power-of-2 sizes return true regardless of element type             │
│ validity.\n\n5. **Conclusion**: Moving the power-of-2 check earlier fixes   │
│ the assertion by correctly identifying that size 2 is power-of-2, allowing  │
│ `ReuseShuffleIndices` for such cases. This maintains correctness because    │
│ power-of-2 vector sizes don't require padding, satisfying the assertion's   │
│ intent."                                                                    │
